,"1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","Kempston, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Kempston, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Barford, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Barford, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Barford, Kempston Parish, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England"},"en":{"1487–1565":"1487–1565","1483–1533":"1483–1533","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1 January 1514":"1 January 1514","about 1525":"about 1525","1565":"1565","1487":"1487","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","Kempston, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Kempston, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Barford, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Barford, Kempston Parish, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Odell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Odell, a place in Bedfordshire, which derives from Old English <i>wād</i> ‘woad’ (a plant collected for the blue dye that could be obtained from it) + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. The spelling <i>O'Dell</i> is not Irish, but a creation by folk etymology, found first among English migrants to Limerick. Compare   Waddell  . — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau does not distinguish between the surnames <i>O'Dell</i> and   Odell  .","Altered form of Swedish   Odell  , as if of Irish origin."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Dell","meanings":["English: habitational name from Odell, a place in Bedfordshire, which derives from Old English <i>wād</i> ‘woad’ (a plant collected for the blue dye that could be obtained from it) + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. The spelling <i>O'Dell</i> is not Irish, but a creation by folk etymology, found first among English migrants to Limerick. Compare   Waddell  . — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau does not distinguish between the surnames <i>O'Dell</i> and   Odell  .","Altered form of Swedish   Odell  , as if of Irish origin."]},{"name":"Waddell","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Wedale near Galashiels (Selkirkshire). This was also the old name of the parish of Stow in Midlothian. The placename may be from Old English <i>wēoh</i> ‘heathen shrine’ (and if so, an example which is unusually far north, and therefore Old English <i>wēod</i> ‘weed, herb’ might be preferred) + <i>dæl</i> ‘hollow, dell’.","English: habitational name from Wadden Hall in Waltham (Kent). The placename may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Wæda</i> (genitive <i>Wæden</i>) or Old English <i>wāden</i> ‘growing with woad’ + Old English <i>halh</i> ‘nook, corner of land’.","English: perhaps a habitational name from Woodhill Park in Clyffe Pypard (Wiltshire). The placename derives from Old English <i>wād</i> ‘woad’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. Alternatively, this name might derive from a hypothetical Middle English personal name <i>Wadel</i> (Old English <i>Wædel</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Katherine ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Dale","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, originally a local name for someone who lived in a <i>dale</i> or valley. It is now fairly commonly used as a given name, along with other monosyllabic surnames of topographical origin (see for example   Dell   and   Hale  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine Dale Odell was born in 1487, in Barford, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Glover Cranfield Sr. in 1512, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1565, in Kempston, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1487–1565":"1487–1565","1483–1533":"1483–1533","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1 January 1514":"1. jaanuar 1514","about 1525":"umbes 1525","1565":"1565","1487":"1487","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England","Kempston, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Kempston, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barford, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Barford, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barford, Kempston Parish, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1487–1565":"1487–1565","1483–1533":"1483–1533","1514–1570":"1514–1570","1525–1614":"1525–1614","1525":"1525","1514":"1514","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1 January 1514":"1. tammikuuta 1514","about 1525":"noin 1525","1565":"1565","1487":"1487","1483":"1483","1570":"1570","1614":"1614","Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barford, Bedfordshire, England":"Barford, Bedfordshi